<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-63-0902 </DOCNO><TEXT>This report describes ongoing and planned Canadian transportation researchand development projects reported by government departments and agencies.The specific field of investigation is the road mode, including vehiclesand related infrastructure. Information given under each project includesnames of participating agencies, personnel, starting and completion dates,purpose of project, description of project, and anticipated impact. Specificprojects include electric vehicles, energy efficiency, urban transportsystems, vanpooling, alternate energy sources for transport, analysisof industrial location implications for transport energy requirements,transport and storage of hazardous energy commodities, hybrid vehicles,improved materials for automobiles, lubricants, computerized vehiclerouting, insulation of highways over permafrost, design of bridges andhighways, and cost analysis of alternative urban transportation programs.</TEXT></DOC>